Ideo preceptum est vicecomiti quod venire faciat eum etc. Postea venit predictus Henricus et finem fecit cum domino per xxd prout patet in rotulis de extractis. Ideo nichil ulterius de eo.

Henry de Hickhng, steward to Thomas Wake of Liddel, Lord of Cropton‚ gave two oak branches to one John de Monmouth without livery of the foresters contrary to the assize of the forest. He is summoned, appears and makes composition for 1S 8d as appears in the Estreat Rolls. F urther proceedings are stayed against him.
